Cuthbert Reeves Kempe (10 February 1856 – 18 April 1953) was an English cricketer.  Kempe's batting and bowling styles are unknown.  He was born at Long Ashton, Somerset.
Kempe made 2 first-class appearances for Gloucestershire in 1877 against Surrey at The Oval and Sussex at the County Ground, Hove.  In his 2 first-class matches, Kempe scored 28 runs at a batting average of 9.33, with a high score of 15.  In the field he took a single catch.He died in Weston-super-Mare, Somerset on 18 April 1953, aged 97.
